The paper deals with the design and implementation of a decentralized crowdsourcing system that ensures privacy and anonymity. This involves resolving the tension between blockchain transparency and data confidentiality, and preventing identity breach and data leakage. The paper also introduces a novel cryptographic notion. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.DB (Databases).
